# Plan: Expose Span Attributes/Data in Trace and Span Views

Issue: https://github.com/getsentry/cli/issues/736

## Summary

Expose full span attributes in `trace view` by fetching per-span details from
the trace-items endpoint. Auto-enabled in `--json` mode (the main use case from
the issue). Opt-in via `--full` for human mode. `span view` already includes
attributes — just refactor shared code out of it.

## Key Design Decisions

- **Auto-enable in `--json` mode** — directly solves the issue; JSON consumers
  (agents, scripts) get complete data without needing to discover a flag
- **`--full` flag for human mode** — explicit opt-in since human output only
  shows a summary count of attributes anyway
- **JSON key is `data`** — consistent with existing `span view --json` output
- **No artificial cap** — `--full` means full. Fetch details for ALL spans in
  the tree. Progress on stderr keeps the user informed; Ctrl+C is always an option
- **Progress on stderr** — `log.info("Fetching span data (N/M)...")` for traces
  with >20 spans. Safe for JSON since stderr ≠ stdout
- **Informational warning for large traces** — when >500 spans, log a warning:
  `"Trace has N spans — this may take a moment. Use 'sentry span view' for
  specific spans."` (not a hard limit, just information)

**Behavior matrix:**

| Command | Fetches details? | Notes |
|---------|-----------------|-------|
| `trace view <id>` | No | Fast, no extra API calls |
| `trace view <id> --json` | Yes (auto, all) | Progress on stderr |
| `trace view <id> --full` | Yes (explicit, all) | Human output notes count |
| `trace view <id> --full --json` | Yes | Same as `--json` alone |

